        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 1 at 4:13PM PDT by NWS Pendleton OR</headline>
        <description>At 413 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Sisters, or 17 miles northwest of Bend, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Sisters.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
